		<li id="comment-721" class="comment byuser comment-author-cbraz even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-721" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn">cbraz</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/10/16/the-pharaohs-vase/#comment-721">
							<time datetime="2010-10-22T16:38:26+00:00">
								October 22, 2010 at 4:38 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>This was lovely. I enjoyed it a lot. As elementalsystems says, it is very reminiscent of a certain kind of movie. For some reason, I had the Pink Panther movies in mind (probably the trench coat &#8211; to which I attached a moustache in my head, and the pharoah&#8217;s vase which makes it all mysterious) so it felt very light-hearted in that vein. </p>
<p>I also wanted a bit more on the inspector. It felt a little uneven, as there was so much exposition about the uniform, and the paragraphs describing the initial discovery that the vase is gone are also very descriptive. But I love the last paragraph. I think it is a perfect ending.</p>
<p>I didn&#8217;t mind the double tug in the first paragraph, but don&#8217;t like the double my in the second tug sentence <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> For me, you could leave the whole unwashed collar bit out to make space for more inspector description. It&#8217;s connotations (sweaty, stained, yellowing, possibly lice-ridden) make me cringe slightly which doesn&#8217;t quite fit the rest of the vibe.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

